          "body": "The chapter ends not with theology but with portraiture. God goes up (17:22). Abraham does not call a family meeting, does not consult Sarah, does not delay a week to prepare. *In the very same day* (17:23, 26) — the phrase is repeated for emphasis — he takes Ishmael, every male servant born in the house, every male bought with money, circumcises them all and himself, at ninety-nine. The wound is real; the cost is real; the dignity loss is real. But the obedience is *immediate*. The chapter that began with God's *walk before Me and be blameless* (17:1) ends with Abraham walking before God in the most concrete possible obedience — flesh cut, household marked, son included, all in one day."
